        <h3>You have a product and a price. Your competitor has the same thing. So why would anyone choose you?</h3>
        <p>Most brands reach for a discount here. It works once. Then customers start waiting for the sale, margins quietly erode, and full price starts feeling like a lie. The answer isn't a better discount. It's a real offer that makes perceived value feel bigger than the price tag.</p>
