        <span class="problem-number">03</span>
        <h3>60% of your traffic lands on a single product page, on a phone, and can't find what they actually need.</h3>
        <p>These aren't browsers. They're evaluators. They came from an ad or a Google result. They've done their homework. But if the product they landed on isn't quite right, and your page doesn't guide them anywhere useful in three taps or less, they bounce to Amazon. They never find the thing that would have converted them.</p>
        <p>Most sites build product discovery for desktop. Sidebars, hover states, dense filter menus. On mobile those become obstacles, not helpers.</p>
