        <h3>You've been testing. The needle won't move. That usually means the problem isn't friction. It's the offer itself.</h3>
        <p>Your customers can find the cart button just fine. They leave because they're not convinced the value is worth the price. Not because the UX is broken. Because the offer is.</p>
