<section class="process" id="process">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">How We Work</span>
    <h2>We look at your data before we say anything.</h2>

    <div class="process-steps">
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="step-number">01</span>
        <h3>We look at your data first.</h3>
        <p>Not to be thorough. Because every site has something obviously wrong that nobody's had time to look at. We pull GA4, Shopify, your ad accounts. We look for the gap between what the data says and what the team believes. Usually we find something in the first week.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="step-number">02</span>
        <h3>We build the test around what we find.</h3>
        <p>Not best practices. Not a playbook. What your data says about your shoppers: where they drop, what they skip, which entry points are bleeding. That's the hypothesis. That's what gets tested.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="step-number">03</span>
        <h3>We test before anything becomes permanent.</h3>
        <p>Proper A/B tests. Real sample sizes. Statistical significance. RPV as the north star, not just conversion rate. The goal isn't to win a test. It's to learn something true about your customers and act on it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="step-number">04</span>
        <h3>We compound.</h3>
        <p>One test teaches you something. A year of tests, properly sequenced, changes the business. Every winner feeds the next hypothesis. The longer the program runs, the harder it becomes for a competitor to catch up. You're building institutional knowledge, not just launching features.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="process-cta-box">
      <div>
        <h3>Ready to see what this looks like for your business?</h3>
        <p>Take the 2-minute quiz. We'll match you to the right starting point.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/quiz/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Where Should I Start?</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

